Webb Simpson  moved into the lead at
the U.S. Open when Jim Furyk bogeyed the par-5 16th hole,
leaving Simpson alone atop the leaderboard at 1 over par.  Simpson, 26, an American who is playing in his second U.S.
Open, finished the fourth round with a score of 281 at San
Franciscoâ€™s Olympic Club.  Furyk, 42, who won the 2003 U.S. Open, is trying to become
the oldest player to win the tournament since Payne Stewart in
